			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Papermaking Retention Aid</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">助留剂</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Drainage Aids; Sizing Agents; Fillers</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">Drainage Aids; Sizing Agents; Fillers</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Organic chemicals</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Retention aids are substances added to paper pulp to improve the retention of fine, dispersed solids such as clay, calcium carbonate, and other fillers. They are typically cationic polymers used to increase the retention of fine particles and fibers in the pulp, preventing their loss in the water phase. Retention aids help reduce the accumulation of deposits on wet-end equipment surfaces, which can cause paper defects. They are water-soluble branched organic polymers with an excellent retention effect on fine fibers and fillers, enhancing the paper machine runnability and the quality of the final paper product.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">助留剂是添加到纸浆中的物质，用于提高细小分散固体（如粘土、碳酸钙和其他填料）的留着率。它们通常是阳离子聚合物，用于提高纸浆中细小颗粒和纤维的留着率，防止它们在水相中流失。助留剂有助于减少湿部设备表面沉积物的积累，沉积物会导致纸张缺陷。它们是水溶性支链有机聚合物，对细纤维和填料有极佳的助留效果，可提高造纸机的运行性能和最终纸品的质量。</common:generalComment>
		</dataSetInformation>
